[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Deciding on setup requirements**\n\nI need to determine if additional setup is necessary. The OGNL expression language may only depend on javassist at runtime, with no need for Docker. There's a system property/security manager to consider, so maybe I should adjust jvmArgs with `--add-opens` for existing paths. The failure in Java run might be due to SecurityManager methods being removed in JDK 25. It's crucial to explore if extra configuration is required before achieving meaningful test coverage, especially with OGNL's dependency on javassist and module access.\n\n**Investigating OGNL security manager**\n\nOGNL 3.3 introduced the \"OgnlSecurityManager,\" which is controlled by the system property `ognl.security.manager`. I’m wondering if the Java run might fail on JDK 25 due to the removal of `System.getSecurityManager`. Let’s check the release notes for insights and inspect the source code for relevant constants. Should I download the source code to a temporary location? The tool seems fine without needing to modify the repository. I'll use bash to handle the download.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c2098af93d312eb016a3faedfd7b0819787f37e528acd6721\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP67oYfIElb-0HvREYKw_AuAeuW8GcbkND4kK5OJInkqYVEpKeWassFiol6IJITVt_UaD1yJGHur9WT0EoWtcDcX-XKBGOcHTSi2F5xNM6NuNjMDSOoB18WN2NbHcQQ7tZTUC-uRc-XHgaGsY8zQzIncEmTZY3CHGS7G9fsUFvLCkA2Njt_jbCfUpgU9BM-snLdbij1V1oQtgExe3yewujHb3hMnJeRX_wVI8Q6ERqhxOsIYAvstEoV15FIYl80HUxEJ9NutWp34DJlbPtisrlurEFpckbOaDfxCw96We7EsJLo3IHYpdENMButD2_yG_NL3efa3esEtby0rH8OBzAIqfTflOZ5Aa3P9v0XnAg4fxsUj2_xGHUd-hgADnPnHicg8bJav0xK6IlEO-tA4GMijOLG30pw-Op8KiMn2Dts8uUNC6uS7MeYu5oFaXJSZ9Zj3T1nnY5zUK1dt5bB1eMArKnikUIxVQEs8GAMWl-gfoGz04CVhwdaK6X6dsJHefZBspcMpjoDxrFM2ChUII_l2IyaevgibPKN6f6vRxZoz-CPveMTAJQxdUS5JAaqAryyyPyDkzcE2u3DvGz91HCoNR5UySdQLdGh6h0-ea9GxaqzJUgut2PyS9onM58fmfAd